<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_c0102d97-994a-4a36-8e3f-0d668d7526c0" outputclass="ncc-clause"><sptc>B5D3</sptc><title id="_4fdcc729-3ff0-4e98-ba54-c9687d4f2c87">Non-drinking water service</title><archive-num>2019: B5.3</archive-num><clause-variation href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10724_0.2.0.xml" variation="SA" variation-type="REPLACE">SA REPLACE Clause</clause-variation><clause-variation href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10686_0.2.0.xml" variation="NSW" variation-type="REPLACE">NSW REPLACE Clause</clause-variation><subclause id="_cbafe06c-0ed3-4a6b-bf98-b615b7bd84e6" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_094ef3df-7fe1-45b6-a571-7c794453ad5e">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A hazard exists wherever it is possible for water or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1228_0.6.0.xml#_a7483c3c-cd8a-4c37-8f2b-8e4fba0e0989" id="_6768a3fe-7531-4d83-917a-b5d1eeef7952" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">contaminants</xref> to enter a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_640028e6-d56b-4b47-9078-6e41be686ba1" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service or supply via any potential or actual <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1233_1.0.0.xml#_b3f409ec-8f72-48d9-8a64-0dc9d5fb5d67" id="_54db4b11-e9b5-46e9-b4e0-e505ea05d356" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">cross-connection</xref> between itself and another separate <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_676fc9da-43c5-47d8-b890-bf450d6bc889" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service on the same <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_f5d84d49-5cd9-448e-ba4c-4461d2737a23" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">site</xref>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_9dc16f51-0545-45e1-903e-8d8af53624fd" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_26f68189-265f-457e-911f-d6b1ca9bb255">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Each hazard must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_1ffa2594-4d2e-4ced-98b8-44d84806fbe2">be assigned a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1332_3.6.0.xml#_e221b82c-bc4b-43d2-ab64-522dd5dd1885" id="_916d5296-bbfb-45fe-838e-73cf91cec12b" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">Hazard Rating</xref> in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9560_0.38.0.xml#_49ef982c-45dc-4a90-9596-f2b6fa0712a5" id="_39ba0cf2-cecb-441f-bdc8-e170c51af779" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">B5D7(10)</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9560_0.38.0.xml#_637c1753-6579-4f76-ab3e-826e43429458" id="_30b76952-b7b5-4a6b-864e-50e8f3c4b794" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">B5D7(11)</xref> or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9560_0.38.0.xml#_1c32bfcf-d609-42b0-981b-f4ea31656712" id="_a6c2b0ce-045b-4b0a-873d-7da134fb5400" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">B5D7(12)</xref>; and</li><li id="_d7f4f1ca-5b59-4016-bebd-01d8dbd6bc5a">be isolated from the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_d4d51cf8-bab6-4970-9d46-5fa99a471b17" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service by appropriate protection which is selected and installed in accordance with AS/NZS 3500.1.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_b28a782e-5a9a-4a5d-aa0f-2f7e0426456d"><callout-type ncc-info-type="exemption"/><p>B5D3 is not applicable to <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_cb8be2f6-6e86-459c-9cc8-a67a61e6f871" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service used for agricultural purposes where the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_f6e1fe67-a07d-487d-b950-f8cbfc911435" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service is supplied solely by <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_20ab24ee-5016-48d9-b613-8e15503593d3" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service(s) and is fully independent from any other water service.</p></callout><callout id="_1375ef7e-98bd-44e6-9cd8-756b36014ee7"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>For the purposes of B5D3, a ‘separate’ <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_9780fc97-7c93-42e8-9bde-ec1254808c65" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service exists where multiple <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_6aa03955-e6fb-452c-a0a1-7f31c19e2c58" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> services are on the same <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_04e5c29a-1f46-4a0d-8e9f-a16d9b62ed34" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">site</xref> and each is supplied by water from different sources.</p><p>For example, on a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_d951bd0d-816b-4fb1-b579-12bd5119a2b9" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">site</xref> connected to both recycled water and bore water, both may be considered <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_45ac2892-3908-41e3-8d5a-dcef7aac507a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> services and are supplied by different sources. Therefore, each is a ‘separate’ <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_caf21eaf-2366-4a4c-99f8-1744ef7e721a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service.</p></callout></clause>